@node Usage
How to use
~~~~~~~~~~
ViewPNM can be started from Workbench or Shell. If You start it from a
Shell the below listed arguments are allowed. Type 'ViewPNM ?' and all
available arguments are shown:


    FILENAME/M,W=WAIT/K/N,M=MODEID/K/N,R=SCREENREQ/S,V=VERBOSE/S:

    @{" FILENAME  " link FILENAME}

    @{" WAIT      " link WAIT}

    @{" MODEID    " link MODEID}

    @{" SCREENREQ " link SCREENREQ}

    @{" VERBOSE   " link VERBOSE}

If ViewPNM is started from  Workbench,  You  can  set  values  to  the
Tooltypes  'WAIT', 'MODEID', 'SCREENREQ' and 'VERBOSE', which have the
same meaning as they have in Shellstart.

Pressing a key or a mousebutton will  close  the  Screen  and  ViewPNM
fetches  the  next  File  (in  Pattern  Matching  mode) or pops up the
Filerequester again. Press the <ESC> key or  select  'Cancel'  in  the
File/ScreenRequest to abort the program.
@endnode

@node FILENAME
FILENAME:

      Simply the name of the picture you want to see. If  no  Filename
      is   entered,   a   Filerequester  will  appear.  AmigaDos-style
      pattern-matching is also supported.
@endnode

@node WAIT
WAIT:

      This is the optional duration time in seconds, an image will  be
      displayed. Useful for slideshows.
@endnode

@node MODEID
MODEID:

      If You want to force the image display Screen to a specific  ID,
      You  have to set a vailid ScreenModeID for an Picasso 8/15/16/24
      Bit Screen. The ID has to be for an 15-,16- or 24Bit  Screen  if
      the  image is a PPM or a PGM file and for an 8 Bit Screen if the
      image is a PBM file. Look out for the utility 'VScreenID'  which
      helps  getting  the IDs. If You choose an ID which nominal sizes
      are  smaller  than  the  picture,  the   Screen   will   be   an
      AutoScrolling  one  if  possible. If the pictures dimensions are
      too big  to  display,  it  will  be  cropped.  If  the  pictures
      dimensions  are  smaller  than  the Screen, it will be displayed
      centered.
@endnode

@node SCREENREQ
SCREENREQ:

      Since version 1.4 ViewPNM tries to find a suitable Screenmode by
      itself.  If You don't like that Screenmode, the switch SCREENREQ
      will induce ViewPNM to open a Screenmode requester where You can
      select Your favourite VillageScreen.
@endnode

@node VERBOSE
VERBOSE:

      By default no messages are printed out, even  errormessages  are
      disabled.  If  You  set  VERBOSE,  You will get some information
      about the image, Screen etc.
@endnode


@node Requirement
Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
   - An Amiga Computer with a UNSEGMENTED driven PICASSO II pluged in
   - 'vilintuisup.library' V2.x+
   - Amiga OS2.04+
@endnode

@node Notes
Notes
~~~~~
   - ViewPNM has not been tested on 1BM PICASSOs
   - P1, P2 and P3 formats are not supported
@endnode

@node History
History
~~~~~~~

     @{" V1.0  ->  V1.1 " link History1}
     @{" V1.1  ->  V1.2 " link History2}
     @{" V1.2  -> V1.21 " link History3}
     @{" V1.21 ->  V1.3 " link History4}
     @{" V1.3  -> V1.31 " link History5}
     @{" V1.31 -> V1.32 " link History6}
     @{" V1.32 ->  V1.4 " link History7}
@endnode

@node History1

     V1.0 -> V1.1:  Now Handles PGM-files.
@endnode

@node History2

     V1.1 -> V1.2:  Now Handles PBM-files, added MODEID-Option.
@endnode

@node History3

     V1.2 -> V1.21: fixed Bug by handling very large pics,
                    program now exits if ScreenModeRequest is canceled.
@endnode

@node History4

     V1.21 -> V1.3: Speed improvement by reading the file in blocks of
                    8 imagelines.
                    Added 8Bit displays for 24Bit images using a fixed
                    palette.
                    Doesn't force Screen dimensions to 4:3 aspect any-
                    more.
                    <ESC>-Key now quits program.
                    Support for Workbench ToolTypes.
                    Sundry internal changes/enhancements.
@endnode

@node History5

     V1.3 -> V1.31: exit on <CTRL>+<C> is disabled.
@endnode

@node History6

     V1.31-> V1.32: Thanks to Gerhard Muellers 'gerlib', ixemul.library
                    isn't needed anymore.
                    Opens info window when started by icon if tooltype
                    'VERBOSE' is set.
                    Compiled without '-funroll-loops' for shorter code.
@endnode

@node History7

     V1.32 ->V1.4:  Looks for the best-fit-Screen by itself.
                    Better Screensize handling
                    Fixed Bug, which ocoured when cropping is done
                    twice or more.
                    New Argument 'SCREENREQ' - pops up Screen Requester.
                    New style of the printed infos.
                    Removed some redundant data.
@endnode

